    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, n. <citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>010001</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2016b"/>, p. <citedRange>170</citedRange></bibl>.</p>           
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w>ἥρως</w>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Untel</supplied> héros.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so</supplied> heroized.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale</supplied> eroe.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>فلان جُعل بطلاً.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Inscriptions including the words <foreign rend="italic">heros/heroissa</foreign> are not many in Cyrenaica. Most of them are votive reliefs. For another base, 
                    see <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.397.html">IRCyr2020 C.397</ref> and the reliefs with heroized riders <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.466.html">IRCyr2020 C.466</ref>, <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.467.html">
                    IRCyr2020 C.467</ref> and probably <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr118600</ref>.</p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
